tools.description:
List up to 10 Sendmarc accounts accessible with the current API key.
Returns an array of up to 10 account objects, each with uuid, name, email, and status fields.
Use this to enumerate all accounts you have access to for reporting or selection.
Optional parameter:
  - limit (number): The maximum number of accounts to return (default 10, max 100).
Example input: { limit: 5 }
Example output:
{
  accounts: [
    { uuid: "...", name: "Acme Corp", email: "admin@acme.com", status: "active" },
    ...
  ]
}

Get details for a specific Sendmarc account.
Returns an object with an 'account' key containing the account object (uuid, name, email, status, and other metadata fields).
Use this to audit or report on a particular account's configuration and status.
Parameters:
  - accountUuid (string): The UUID of the account to fetch.
Example input: { accountUuid: "..." }
Example output:
{
  "account": {
    "uuid": "...",
    "name": "Acme Corp",
    "email": "admin@acme.com",
    "status": "active"
    // ... other fields ...
  }
}
